A measure of performance was reported with ISR-1. In tests, it was considered thatbefore each resume operation on a client a reboot should be executed to ensure a coldNFS cache. Two types of suspend events were considered: warm suspend, which occursin a VM shortly after a resume event, and cold suspend, which occurs long after aresume event. A cold resume takes 125 seconds, a warm suspend 114 seconds, anda cold suspend 146 seconds. These results are tolerable for some users but generallymuch longer than suspend resume in a laptop.
